{"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Basic","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Tactic.NoMatch","Lean.Elab.Command"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L270-L271","name":"clearAuxDecl","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#clearAuxDecl","doc":"This tactic clears all auxiliary declarations from the context. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L263-L267","name":"triv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#triv","doc":"Tries to solve the goal using a canonical proof of `True`, or the `rfl` tactic.\nUnlike `trivial` or `trivial'`, does not use the `contradiction` tactic.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L260-L260","name":"tacticEapply_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticEapply_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L257-L257","name":"tacticFapply_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticFapply_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L240-L240","name":"tacticAny_goals_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticAny_goals_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L236-L236","name":"tacticRepeat'_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticRepeat'_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L226-L234","name":"repeat'Aux","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#repeat'Aux","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L205-L217","name":"tacticIterate____","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticIterate____","doc":"`iterate n tac` runs `tac` exactly `n` times.\n`iterate tac` runs `tac` repeatedly until failure.\n\nTo run multiple tactics, one can do `iterate (tac₁; tac₂; ⋯)` or\n```lean\niterate\n  tac₁\n  tac₂\n  ⋯\n```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L194-L194","name":"byContra","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#byContra","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L188-L188","name":"tacticMatch_target_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticMatch_target_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L163-L186","name":"evalGuardHyp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#evalGuardHyp","doc":"Check that a named hypothesis has a given type and/or value.\n\n`guardHyp h : t` checks the type up to syntactic equality,\nwhile `guardHyp h :ₐ t` checks the type up to alpha equality.\n`guardHyp h := v` checks value up to syntactic equality,\nwhile `guardHyp h :=ₐ v` checks the value up to alpha equality. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L153-L154","name":"guardHyp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#guardHyp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L144-L147","name":"guardTargetStrict","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#guardTargetStrict","doc":"Check the target agrees (syntactically) with a given expression.\nSee also `guardTarget` and `guardTarget'` for testing\nup to alpha equality and definitional equality. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L136-L139","name":"guardExprStrict","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#guardExprStrict","doc":"Check syntactic equality of two expressions.\nSee also `guardExprEq` and `guardExprEq'` for testing\nup to alpha equality and definitional equality. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L128-L131","name":"exacts","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#exacts","doc":"Like `exact`, but takes a list of terms and checks that all goals are discharged after the tactic.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L125-L126","name":"tacticAssumption'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticAssumption'","doc":"Try calling `assumption` on all goals; succeeds if it closes at least one goal. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L120-L123","name":"evalIntrov.intro1PStep","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#evalIntrov.intro1PStep","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L112-L119","name":"evalIntrov.introsDep","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#evalIntrov.introsDep","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L103-L123","name":"evalIntrov","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#evalIntrov","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L70-L102","name":"introv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#introv","doc":"The tactic `introv` allows the user to automatically introduce the variables of a theorem and\nexplicitly name the non-dependent hypotheses.\nAny dependent hypotheses are assigned their default names.\n\nExamples:\n```\nexample : ∀ a b : Nat, a = b → b = a := by\n  introv h,\n  exact h.symm\n```\nThe state after `introv h` is\n```\na b : ℕ,\nh : a = b\n⊢ b = a\n```\n\n```\nexample : ∀ a b : Nat, a = b → ∀ c, b = c → a = c := by\n  introv h₁ h₂,\n  exact h₁.trans h₂\n```\nThe state after `introv h₁ h₂` is\n```\na b : ℕ,\nh₁ : a = b,\nc : ℕ,\nh₂ : b = c\n⊢ a = c\n```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L60-L60","name":"tacticTransitivity__","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticTransitivity__","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L57-L57","name":"classical","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#classical","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L50-L54","name":"tacticBy_cases_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticBy_cases_","doc":"`by_cases p` makes a case distinction on `p`,\nresulting in two subgoals `h : p ⊢` and `h : ¬ p ⊢`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L43-L47","name":"«tacticBy_cases_:_»","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#«tacticBy_cases_:_»","doc":"`by_cases h : p` makes a case distinction on `p`,\nresulting in two subgoals `h : p ⊢` and `h : ¬ p ⊢`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L36-L37","name":"tacticRwa__","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticRwa__","doc":"`rwa` calls `rw`, then closes any remaining goals using `assumption`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L24-L24","name":"tactic_","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tactic_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L22-L22","name":"tacticExfalso","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#tacticExfalso","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L19-L19","name":"command_Lemma___","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#command_Lemma___","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L13-L17","name":"elabVariables","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#elabVariables","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.lean#L11-L11","name":"variables","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Basic.html#variables","doc":""}]}